Node.Notes: This clause "Who will hear (us)?" is probably what the treacherous plotters of evil think.
Uncertain. Most follow ancient versions and some Hebrew manuscripts and read "my" Strength instead of "his" strength.
Sense of cause to look (in triumph).
As with previous cases, uncertain whether enemies/slanderers/ambushers.
Many omit the negative, but negative can be explained as "Do not kill them (outright)" (instead defeating them and leaving them lingering in weakness).
Cause to move to and fro, could be in sense of make wander/homeless or make stagger/totter.
Most translate as "O Lord, our shield," but word order is reverse of what is normally expected in Hebrew). Probably clause supplying reason for God to act:: "[you are] our shield, O Lord."
Text reads "spend the night," which could be the sense of stay all night. Many revocalize to yield "they howl."
Possible that "God" is S instead of vocative. Tree assumes "O God, [you are] my fortress, [you are] the God who shows me steadfast love."
